Your problem is that in `i/fact` as well as in `(sign*i)/fact` all operands are `ints` and thus you _will_ get 0 as the result of that calculation (1/2 etc. is 0 in [integer math](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3602827/what-is-the-behavior-of-integer-division) and so will be `i/i!` with the exception of `1/1!`and `2/2!` because that&#39;s just `1/1` and `2/2`). When using `Math.pow(-1,i)` you get a `double` and now the calculation works. 

So to fix your code use a cast to `double`:

    if (i%2==0)
         sum += (double)i/fact;
    else 
